d unto Barnabas, Let us go again and visit our brethren in every city where we have preached the word of the Lord, and see how they do.","year":51},{"id":"recaXiONwm17qRKCO","ref":"Acts.15.37","text":"And Barnabas determined to take with them John, whose surname was Mark.","year":51},{"id":"recVNaio13RoAMUn6","ref":"Acts.15.38","text":"But Paul thought not good to take him with them, who departed from them from Pamphylia, and went not with them to the work.","year":51},{"id":"recXFi5gfBuHBckS5","ref":"Acts.15.39","text":"And the contention was so sharp between them, that they departed asunder one from the other: and so Barnabas took Mark, and sailed unto Cyprus;","year":51}]}
